# .gitignore — a little list that tells Git which files to ignore.
#
# Git is the tool that remembers the history of your project, like a
# save button that never forgets. But some files are junk your computer
# makes on its own, and a few hold private secrets. You don't want those
# saved. This file is the "please skip these" note, and Git obeys it.
#
# You don't need to understand every line yet. Lesson 06 walks you
# through Git slowly: lessons/06-saving-work-with-git.md
#
# One rule to remember: a name ending with a slash ( / ) means a folder.

# Junk files your computer creates automatically (safe to ignore).
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Downloaded code libraries — big, and easy to get again anytime.
node_modules/

# Secret settings like passwords and keys. Never share these. Ever.
.env
.env.*

# Settings folders for your code editor — yours, not part of the project.
.vscode/
.idea/

# Log files — scratch notes some programs write while they run.
*.log
